pi-doctor for Debian
====================

This source package builds the `pi-doctor` Rust workspace binary from the
repository root.

The upstream source intentionally excludes generated support bundles, local
build products, release archives, documentation site output, and temporary
directories. Those paths are listed in `debian/copyright` and guarded again by
`debian/source/options`.

Before uploading to mentors.debian.net:

* File an ITP bug against the `wnpp` pseudo-package and add the real
  `Closes: #NNNNNN` entry to `debian/changelog`.
* Build the source package with `dpkg-buildpackage -S -sa`.
* Build the binary package in a clean unstable chroot with `sbuild` or `pbuilder`.
* Run `lintian --pedantic` on the `.changes` file.
* Run `autopkgtest` against the built source or `.changes` file.
* Sign the upload with the GPG key configured on mentors.debian.net.
